### register
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret-pass",
  "name": "Alice"
}

> {%
client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
client.global.set("userId", response.body.user.id);
%}

###

### register — duplicate email → 409
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret-pass",
  "name": "Alice"
}

###

### register — short password → 400 validation_failed
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "short"
}

###

### login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret-pass"
}

> {% client.global.set("token", response.body.token); %}

###

### login — wrong password → 401 invalid_credentials
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "wrong-pass-1234"
}

###

### /me with token → 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### /me without token → 401 (empty body)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/me

###

### /me with garbage token → 401
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/me
Authorization: Bearer not-a-jwt
